Central has spent a lot of time attached to the Clear modem although Scott may have been doing something on there for the Meijer debugging just now. North is also getting some specialized reconfiguration also for the Meijer project.

the printer should be connected to the Comcast gateway, meaning it is a peer to Uncorked, North, and when Central is NOT attached to Clear, then it as well. in that setup, it should be findable, and if not, you may need to try to re-find the bugger.

if anyone is having trouble with UNCORKED, I'd like to know about it, since it is fairly cleanly set up and hasn't been proven to my satisfaction to be suspect since Comcast replaced our gateway. in the longer term, we are reviewing bids for a low voltage contractor coming through and running cable throughout the suite, building a real patch panel, and so on. in that universe, we intend to find the appropriately professional gateway, and turn the Comcast one into a dumb connection. Hopefully we will be much happier then.
